Simulated Data Object

simdata.Rd

Simulates proteomic data by randomly generating data for various Bioinformatics related analyses and unit tests. Feature names are randomly generated and have the seq.xxxx.xx format so that downstream tools will function seamlessly. Model types this data can support:

  1. Binary classification

  2. Continuous regression

  3. Survival

Usage

simdata

Format

The format of simdata (100 x 47) is:

id

A sample id number.

class_response

The classification response variable.

reg_response

The regression response variable.

time

The time-to-event variable for survival problems.

status

The event status variable for survival problems.

SampleId

Identical to the id column; for POC tools to run.

SlideId

Randomly generated numeric, used to create rownames.

Subarray

All 1s. Used to create rownames.

SiteId

Locations from LOTR; for POC tools to run.

age

A randomly assigned age variable: 18 - 80.

gender

A randomly assigned gender variable: "F" or "M".

HybControlNormScale

Random continuous data in [0.4, 2.5].

NormScale_40

Random continuous data in [0.4, 2.5].

NormScale_0_005

Random continuous data in [0.4, 2.5].

NormScale_1

Random continuous data in [0.4, 2.5].
